I've just had a customer trying to implement an SSO Authenticator.

He followed this page http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Understanding+User+Management+in+Confluence to this page: http://opensource.atlassian.com/seraph/sso.html which was not completely helpful.  In particular it doesn't contain any Confluence specific information, unlike this page: http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DEV/Single+Sign-on+Integration+with+JIRA+and+Confluence

I have now added a link from the User Management Overview page to the SSO for JIRA and Confluence page, which will hopefully be helpful for future customers, but it's still a little confusing.  In particular nothing really covers how to plug in logging out from SSO.

