When you type a newline in the Rich Text Editor (starting a new paragraph), and then hit the backspace key (removing the newly created paragraph), the editor loses context and jumps to the top of the page. This is disconcerting when you are editing at the bottom of a very large page, as you need to scroll back down to find the place where you were editing.

